==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supernatant
<hw>Su`per*na"tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>supernatanus</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>supernatare</ets> to swim above;
<ets>super</ets> above + <ets>natare</ets> to swim.]</ety> <def>Swimming
above; floating on the surface; <as>as, oil <ex>supernatant</ex> on
water</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supernatant</ent>⟦br⟧
<--

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Supernatant
<hw>Su`per*na"tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The liquid remaining after solids suspended in the liquid have been sedimented by gravity or by centrifugation.  Contrasted with the solid <contr>sediment</contr>, or (in centrifugation) the <contr>pellet</contr>.</def> -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supernatation</ent>⟦br⟧
